## Carpentry and Kashmir homes — local context

Kashmir's climate — cold winters, humid summers, and seasonal rainfall — affects woodwork in ways that generic advice often misses. Moisture can warp door frames, older furniture may need careful restoration rather than replacement, and multi-storey homes in Srinagar often mix old timber construction with newer modular fittings.

When you book through Panun Kaergar, you are hiring a professional who understands residential carpentry in local homes. Providers on our platform arrive with proper tools and can advise whether a repair is enough or new material is needed. You can describe the issue in the app — a wardrobe door that will not close, a window that jams after rain, a shelf that needs custom sizing for an awkward alcove — and the assigned carpenter comes prepared for the visit.

For families preparing for weddings, Eid gatherings, or guests from outside Kashmir, small carpentry fixes — a wobbly chair, a sticking drawer, a loose cabinet handle — make a noticeable difference. Panun Kaergar's review system also helps the community identify carpenters who consistently deliver quality work across Srinagar.

