## Tips before your carpenter visit in Srinagar

A little preparation helps your booking go smoothly and saves time on site:

- **Clear access** to the furniture, door, window, or room where work is needed.
- **Take photos** of the problem before the visit — useful when booking via WhatsApp or the website.
- **List all tasks** in one booking if they are in the same visit — for example, a sticking door and a loose cabinet hinge.
- **Note dimensions** if you need custom shelving or a cabinet modification, so the carpenter can plan materials.
- **Be home or have someone available** to show the work areas and approve the approach.

If the job requires materials — new hinges, handles, plywood, or hardware — your provider can advise on what is needed. Some carpenters carry common parts; for specialised items, they may recommend local purchase or a follow-up visit once materials are ready.

